				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-757315#post-4284299</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-757315/scp-1568#post-4284299</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 18 Jun 2019 11:46:27 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>wishun</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1204404</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>The &quot;right side&quot; of a boat is &quot;starboard&quot;. This is a technical term, and goes to proper tone.<br /> But it's also just a bit too close to a style/language choice for me to be comfortable fixing it.</p> <p>Similarly, the paragraph describing -1 needs to have the phrase &quot;the current instance of -1&quot; added somewhere and probably rearranged a bit. As written, it's saying that every -1 is identical. So either the crab seeks out identical boats, which shouldn't exist. Or it alters the appearance of each new &quot;shell&quot; it inhabits. Which I really don't think was the intent.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
